{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_016jELRmBXPbBrZgP2EB45qe","type":"tool_result","content":"   336→### Decision 6: Retro-to-Sprint Pipeline — Tech Debt as First-Class Work\n   337→\n   338→**Problem:** Session retros produce action items that never get actioned. Tech debt accumulates silently. No mechanism to feed retro findings back into the sprint.\n   339→\n   340→**Decision:** Three mechanisms embedded in the sprint cycle:\n   341→\n   342→**6a. Persistent epic-TD:**\n   343→- `epic-TD` in sprint-state.json is never marked `done`\n   344→- New stories append to it from any source (retro, audit, manual)\n   345→- harness-run Step 5 skips epic completion for `epic-TD`\n   346→\n   347→**6b. Retro auto-creates stories (Step 8b):**\n   348→- After session retro writes the markdown file, harness-run parses `## 6. Action Items`\n   349→- `### Fix Now` and `### Fix Soon` items become `TD-N-slug: backlog` stories\n   350→- Deduplication: normalize text, compare against existing TD story titles (80% word overlap = skip)\n   351→- `### Backlog` items go to `tech-debt-backlog.md` for tracking only\n   352→\n   353→**6c. Tech debt gate (Step 2 priority):**\n   354→- Before selecting ANY Tier D (backlog) story from a feature epic, check if `epic-TD` has pending work\n   355→- If yes, process TD stories first\n   356→- This ensures accumulated debt gets addressed before new features start\n   357→\n   358→---\n   359→\n   360→### Decision 7: Error Handling — No More Silent Swallowing\n   361→\n   362→**Problem:** 53 bare `catch {}` blocks. Errors are logged as comments but not propagated. Debugging is impossible because stack traces are lost.\n   363→\n   364→**Decision:** Three error strategies, no fourth:\n   365→\n   366→1. **Result\\<T\\>** for all module-level functions that can fail expectably (file not found, parse error, subprocess failure). Already established — enforce it.\n   367→\n   368→2. **Typed errors** for domain-specific failures:\n   369→```typescript\n   370→class BeadsNotInstalledError extends Error { ... }\n   371→class DockerNotAvailableError extends Error { ... }\n   372→class StateCorruptedError extends Error { ... }\n   373→class StackNotSupportedError extends Error { ... }\n   374→```\n   375→\n   376→3. **Explicit ignore with reason** for truly non-fatal cases:\n   377→```typescript\n   378→try { ... }\n   379→catch {\n   380→  // IGNORE: cleanup failure is non-fatal — container may already be removed\n   381→}\n   382→```\n   383→\n   384→**Banned:** `catch { }`, `catch { return null }`, `catch { /* fallthrough */ }` without an `// IGNORE:` comment explaining why.\n   385→\n   386→**Enforcement:** ESLint rule `no-empty-catch` + custom rule requiring `// IGNORE:` comment in catch blocks that don't rethrow or return Result.fail().\n   387→\n   388→---\n   389→\n   390→### Decision 8: Command Structure — Thin Commands, Fat Modules\n   391→\n   392→**Problem:** `status.ts` is 744 lines. Commands contain business logic (URL builders, formatters, story drill-down). Not testable without command wiring.\n   393→\n   394→**Decision:** Commands are <100 lines. They parse CLI args, call a module function, format output. All business logic lives in modules.\n   395→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_014CxpRCwC7G8ESMTZo9TkWy","session_id":"e0c38769-c734-43c9-928b-954c93aa963e","uuid":"e1a077ac-3ecc-4e7d-9dda-e17a01fada73","timestamp":"2026-03-24T22:09:08.007Z"}
