{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01YAJz1idgo6SWZvP7VKYD4z","type":"tool_result","content":"30-- `skipped_reasons = []` (list of `{story_key}: {reason}` strings)\n31-- `attempts = 0` (per story, resets for each new story — counts ALL retries: dev failures, review round-trips, verify→dev loops)\n32-- `max_attempts = 10` (single limit for all retry types)\n33-- `start_time = current timestamp`\n34-\n35:## Step 2: Find Next Actionable Story (Cross-Epic Scan)\n36-\n37-Scan ALL stories across ALL epics to find the highest-priority actionable story. Epic boundaries do not constrain selection.\n38-\n39-1. **Collect all stories:** Gather every `N-M-slug` entry from `development_status`, regardless of which epic it belongs to.\n40-\n--\n375-3. **Increment `attempts`.** If `attempts >= max_attempts` (10):\n376-   - Increment `stories_skipped`\n377-   - Append `{story_key}: verify↔dev cycle limit (10)` to `skipped_reasons`\n378-   - Print: `[WARN] Story {story_key}: verify↔dev cycle limit reached — skipping`\n379-   - Run cleanup (step 3d-viii)\n380:   - Go to Step 2 (next story)\n381-\n382-4. **Return story to dev.** Update sprint-status.yaml: change `{story_key}` status from `verifying` to `in-progress`.\n383-\n384-5. **Reset retry count.** Update `ralph/.story_retries`: write/replace the line `{story_key}=0` in the file (read existing file first to preserve other entries). This resets the infra retry budget since the story is going back to dev.\n385-\n--\n408-\n409-4. Retry verification with the fixed infrastructure.\n410-\n411-5. If after 3 infra fix attempts the problem persists, increment `attempts` and move to next story:\n412-   - Print: `[WARN] Story {story_key}: infra problem persists after 3 fix attempts — skipping (attempt {attempts}/{max_attempts})`\n413:   - Go to Step 2\n414-\n415-**The agent must NOT repeatedly retry the same broken infrastructure.** Each retry must include an actual fix attempt.\n416-\n417-**Path C — Escalated ACs due to infra/tooling problems:**\n418-\n--\n472-\n473-1. Increment `stories_completed`\n474-2. Re-read `sprint-status.yaml` to get current state\n475-3. Determine the story's parent epic (epic number N from the story key)\n476-4. Check if all stories in epic N are `done` (every `N-M-slug` has status `done`):\n477:   - If yes → go to Step 5 (epic completion). After Step 5, return to Step 2 for the next cross-epic scan.\n478:   - If no → go directly to Step 2 for the next cross-epic scan (attempts will be reset there for the new story)\n479-\n480-## Step 5: Epic Completion\n481-\n482-All stories in the current epic are done.\n483-\n--\n510-4. Print:\n511-   ```\n512-   [OK] Epic {N}: DONE (all stories complete, retrospective run)\n513-   ```\n514-\n515:5. Return to Step 2 for the next cross-epic scan. Step 2 will determine if more actionable stories exist or if the sprint is complete.\n516-\n517-## Step 6: Failure Handling\n518-\n519-A story has exceeded max_attempts (10). Clear live run progress immediately:\n520-\n--\n523-```\n524-\n525-1. Increment `stories_failed`\n526-2. Increment `stories_skipped`\n527-3. Append `{story_key}: failed ({reason})` to `skipped_reasons` where reason is `retry-exhausted` or `max-cycles-exceeded`\n528:4. Update `ralph/.story_retries`: write/replace the line `{story_key}={attempts}` in the file (read existing file first to preserve other entries). This persists the retry state so future sessions skip this story immediately via the retry-exhausted check in Step 2.\n529-5. Print:\n530-   ```\n531-   [FAIL] Story {story_key}: exceeded {max_attempts} attempts\n532-   [FAIL] Last status: {current_status}\n533-   [INFO] Skipping story — continuing to next actionable story\n534-   ```\n535:6. Go to Step 2 to find the next actionable story. Do NOT halt the sprint. Step 2 will go to Step 7 only when zero actionable stories remain.\n536-\n537-## Step 7: Sprint Execution Summary\n538-\n539-Clear live run progress to ensure clean state before printing summary:\n540-"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_014CxpRCwC7G8ESMTZo9TkWy","session_id":"e0c38769-c734-43c9-928b-954c93aa963e","uuid":"35ee09c2-4db1-4c25-97b7-4afcb71c4604","timestamp":"2026-03-24T22:09:25.835Z"}
