{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01GAEH4HaeS1eW5UR9taZ8z5","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\n\n**Review complete.** Story 14-2 status set to `verifying`.\n\n**What was done:**\n- Adversarial review of `src/modules/sprint/selector.ts` and `src/modules/sprint/__tests__/selector.test.ts`\n- All 9 ACs verified as implemented\n- 3 MEDIUM issues found and fixed:\n  1. `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/modules/sprint/AGENTS.md` — added TD gate documentation\n  2. `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/modules/sprint/__tests__/selector.test.ts` — replaced scope-polluting shorthand variables with typed `it.each`, improved test labels\n  3. Added case-sensitivity test and `ready` status test (2 new test cases)\n- Build passes, 3666 tests pass, 97.1% coverage, all files under 300 lines, all files above 80% per-file floor\n\n## Session Issues\n\n**Bugs found:**\n- None\n\n**Code quality issues found but NOT fixed (LOW priority):**\n- LOW: selector.ts line 103 comment lacks architecture Decision 6c reference\n- LOW: `keyToTitle()` produces \"Td 1 fix\" for \"TD-1-fix\" — acronym gets lowercased. Pre-existing issue, not introduced by this story.\n\n**Coverage gaps:**\n- None. selector.ts has 100% coverage. All 154 source files above 80% floor.\n\n**Architecture concerns:**\n- The TD gate relies on a naming convention (`TD-` prefix) rather than structured metadata. If someone names a story `TD-something` that isn't tech debt, it will be incorrectly prioritized. This is an accepted design tradeoff per Decision 6c but worth noting.\n\n**Items sent back for re-development:**\n- None"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: af6329f5b2e8432c9 (use SendMessage with to: 'af6329f5b2e8432c9' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 43049\ntool_uses: 38\nduration_ms: 385854</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e0c38769-c734-43c9-928b-954c93aa963e","uuid":"83236159-f1d4-4451-a8f8-2f5d82a79de8","